headline: Big bank earnings, Fed commentary: What to Watch Next Week
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton previews several of the biggest stories to come next week, including corporate earnings from a variety of companies like major banks JPMorgan (JPM), Wells Fargo (WFC), Goldman Sachs (GS), Citi (C), Bank of America (BAC), and Morgan Stanley (MS); a slew of commentary from Federal Reserve officials; and the US Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS) working to have September's Consumer Price Index (CPI) inflation data ready by October 24. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: How Recent Bond Issuances at Goldman Sachs (GS) Are Shaping Its Investment Narrative
summary: In early October 2025, Goldman Sachs announced a series of new fixed-income offerings, including several callable and variable rate senior notes with maturities ranging from 2026 to 2040, and completed multiple smaller bond issuances as part of broader funding initiatives.
